**Sample voting app - Cats and Dogs**

This app deploys the sample voting app, Cats and Dogs via pods and services (no deployments or replica sets)
To deploy this app on Kubernetes cluster, do following:

1. From the command line which is connected to Kubernetes cluster (cloud or Minikube), clone the app from Github: *git clone https://github.com/Acovid/kubernetes-example-voting-app.git*
2. Move to the directory with the code: *cd kubernetes-example-voting-app*
3. Create Kubernetes pods and services by running these commands, one after another:
   *kubectl create -f voting-app-pod.yml*
   *kubectl create -f voting-app-service.yml*
   *kubectl create -f redis-pod.yml*
   *kubectl create -f redis-service.yml*
   *kubectl create -f postgres-pod.yml*
   *kubectl create -f postgres-service.yml*
   *kubectl create -f worker-app-pod.yml*
   *kubectl create -f result-app-pod.yml*
   *kubectl create -f result-app-service.yml*
